Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm
wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly
sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with salt and pepper and fry, stirring
occasionally, until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%grams}. Halve the
@burger buns{2}. Cut the @tomato{1%medium}(cut into 1cm chunks).

Add the tomatoes to a large #bowl{} with half the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml},
@?sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Mix together and set
aside for later.

When the onions are golden, turn the heat down slightly and stir in the
@fig jam{40%grams}, @butter{20%grams} and the remaining @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}.
Cook for ~{1%minute}, then remove from the heat and set aside.

When the chips are halfway through cooking, turn them. Sprinkle over the
@hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}(grated) and return to the oven for the
remaining time, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Place the @unconventional plant-based burgers{2} on a lightly oiled baking
tray.

Bake on the middle shelf until browned, ~{8-9%minutes}.

Once browned, carefully place the Cheddar on top of the burgers.

Add the burger buns onto the same tray, then pop back into the oven until the
cheese has melted and the buns are warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, remove your chips from the oven and sprinkle over the
@truffle zest{1%sachet}.

When everything's ready, spread half the @mayonnaise{32%grams} over the bun
bases and lids.

Top the bases with some @baby leaf mix{50%grams} and the cheesy burgers, then
top with the fig jam onions. Sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Toss the remaining baby leaves through the tomatoes to coat in the dressing.

Serve your craft burgers with your truffle chips and salad alongside. Add a
dollop of the remaining @mayonnaise{32%grams} for dipping.

Enjoy!